----------------------------------
Usage:
----------------------------------
fsniffer [-r filename] [-i interface] [-t time] [-o time_offset] [-N num] [-S secs]

This program sniffs TCP, UDP, and ICMP flows on an interface or a caputre
and prints the flow information.


----------------------------------
Compile instructions:
----------------------------------
make clean
make all


----------------------------------
NOTES:
----------------------------------
For ICMP flows, under the state column, the type number of the most recently seen
packet is displayed. The assumption is made that ICMP packets that are to and from the 
same source and destination within the timeout period are apart of the same flow. 


